
[1]legerdemain

   LEG'ERDEMAIN, n. [See Light.]

   Slight of hand; a deceptive performance which depends on dexterity of
   hand; a trick performed with such art and adroitness, that the manner
   or art eludes observation. The word is sometimes used adjectively; as a
   legerdemain trick.
